g.text: UML Diagram: Class Position in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.

a.title: ― Member: Element in a collection that can be either atomic (individual member) or composite (collection).
a.xlink:title: ― Member: Element in a collection that can be either atomic (individual member) or composite (collection).

a.title: ― List: Simple ordered Collection defined as a list of Members where the location of each Member in the list is given by the associated Position class.
a.xlink:title: ― List: Simple ordered Collection defined as a list of Members where the location of each Member in the list is given by the associated Position class.

a.title: ― Position: Position of the associated member within the associated List.
a.xlink:title: ― Position: Position of the associated member within the associated List.

a.title: ― ClassificationItemPosition: Provides a classification item with an index conveying the order of the classification item within a sequence, expressed as an integer, progressing upward from 0 or 1.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationItemPosition: Provides a classification item with an index conveying the order of the classification item within a sequence, expressed as an integer, progressing upward from 0 or 1.

a.title: ― ClassificationIndexEntryPosition: Member indicator for use with member type classification index entry.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationIndexEntryPosition: Member indicator for use with member type classification index entry.

a.title: ― PhysicalRecordSegmentPosition: Assigns a position of the physical record segment within the whole physical record. For example in what order does this 80 character segment fall within an 800 character record.
a.xlink:title: ― PhysicalRecordSegmentPosition: Assigns a position of the physical record segment within the whole physical record. For example in what order does this 80 character segment fall within an 800 character record.

a.title: ― ValueMappingPosition: Denotes the position of a value mapping in a sequence.
a.xlink:title: ― ValueMappingPosition: Denotes the position of a value mapping in a sequence.

a.title: ― AgentPosition: Assigns a sequence number to an agent in an agent listing.
a.xlink:title: ― AgentPosition: Assigns a sequence number to an agent in an agent listing.

a.title: ― CategoryPosition: Assigns a sequence number to a category within a list.
a.xlink:title: ― CategoryPosition: Assigns a sequence number to a category within a list.

a.title: ― ClassificationPosition: The index of a classification within a classification family expressed as an integer, progressing upward from 0 or 1.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationPosition: The index of a classification within a classification family expressed as an integer, progressing upward from 0 or 1.

a.title: ― VariablePosition: Assigns a sequence number to a variable within a list.
a.xlink:title: ― VariablePosition: Assigns a sequence number to a variable within a list.

a.title: ― CodePosition: An index within an order intended for presentation (even though the content within levels of the hierarchy may be conceptually unordered). Expressed as an integer counting upward from 01 or 1.
a.xlink:title: ― CodePosition: An index within an order intended for presentation (even though the content within levels of the hierarchy may be conceptually unordered). Expressed as an integer counting upward from 01 or 1.

a.title: ― ComponentPosition: Indexes the components in a data structure using integers with a position indicated by incrementing upward from 0 or 1.
a.xlink:title: ― ComponentPosition: Indexes the components in a data structure using integers with a position indicated by incrementing upward from 0 or 1.

a.title: ― LogicalRecordPosition: Assigns a position of the logical record within the data store.
a.xlink:title: ― LogicalRecordPosition: Assigns a position of the logical record within the data store.

a.title: ― has: The Position of the member in the list. Lifecycle dependency: position cannot exist without a list and can be related to one and only one list.
a.xlink:title: ― has: The Position of the member in the list. Lifecycle dependency: position cannot exist without a list and can be related to one and only one list.
